Swatch Aims for Sales Exceeding 7 Billion Francs, Le Temps Says

-- B y   T o m   M u l i e r
-- 
2011-03-01T06:53:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/swatch-aims-for-sales-exceeding-7-billion-francs-le-temps-says.html
  Swatch Group AG  is aiming for gross
revenue in 2011 to exceed 7 billion Swiss francs ($7.5 billion),
 Le Temps  said, citing Chief Executive Officer Nick Hayek.  The watchmaker is also targeting annual revenue of 10
billion francs in coming years, mostly through growth of
existing businesses, Hayek told the newspaper. January was the
fourth-best month ever for the company, Le Temps reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Thomas Mulier in Geneva at 
 tmulier@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
